<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am using the Zend_Cloud_StorageService as I am hoping to use the FileSystem adapter on internal servers and the S3 adapter on external servers.</p>

<p>I think it is therefore wrong that Zend_Cloud_StorageService_Adapter_FileSystem::storeItem() requires that the path provided in the first argument already exists within the path specified when instantiating the class.</p>

<p>I expect Zend_Cloud_StorageService_Adapter_FileSystem::storeItem() to behave the same as the S3 adapter, so that it automatically creates those intermediate folders. Therefore I can easily switch between implementations of Zend_Cloud_StorageService_Adapter.</p>

